The paper deals with secure multi-party computation and privacy-preserving data shuffling, which are common topics in the cryptography (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. The use of homomorphic encryption also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
